snippet.textDisplay: I've been with these guys since 2013, meaning i spent 7 years of my life dedicated to them, supporting them non stop. So being a fan since beginning i saw a lot of ups and down ikon went through n I've gotta said, the moment hanbin left, this fandom is not the same anymore. I feel a lot of fans left them. I noticed this when i realised my twitter tl have soo little update on iKON despite me only follow ikon fan acc. Some have change acc to other groups n some choose to deactivate. The lack of update is really concerning because it indicates that ikon is slowly losing fans. I've never felt this way when ikon went hiatus in 2016 to promote in japan. I mean yeah they did lost some fans at the time but never like this. At that time, we still can get ikon content, but this time it's none. Also with ikonic being unstable as a fandom, with some leaving, lost interest n even lazy in streaming. We can't even get 200k views on two vid combine. Even rookies group can do better than that. If this continues, ikon will really be affected at the end. It's really sad how things turn like this for ikon. They start as monster rookie with huge fandom but because of company mismanagement n issues, they had to start all over again. Kinda remind me of bap. But i hope ikon doesn't go the path that bap goes. I pray they will rise again someday.

I felt sorry that I couldn't go to the audience of 'Dive' but I was happy to see it because I filmed it from various angles, as if I were on the scene, even when I saw it from a hidden track. This album was a combination of the group iKON's three beats. Nevertheless, it was so sad that I couldn't go to see iKON, and there were few active broadcasts, but thanks to the hidden track that showed the children live for nearly two hours, I felt less sorry. And I think it was good because there were many people congratulating for June's birthday. 'Dive' can express what group iKON is, from choreography to singing. I dare to say that it's a song that only iKON can do. This video proves it. So, thanks to Hidden Track, which shared 'Dive' on YouTube, I'm glad the album is reaching out to more people. I felt sorry that I couldn't go to the audience of 'Dive' but I was happy to see it because I filmed it from various angles, as if I were on the scene, even when I saw it from a hidden track. This album was a combination of the group iKON's three beats. Nevertheless, it was so sad that I couldn't go to see iKON, and there were few active broadcasts, but thanks to the hidden track that showed the children live for nearly two hours, I felt less sorry. And I think it was good because there were many people congratulating for June's birthday. 'Dive' can express what group iKON is, from choreography to singing. I dare to say that it's a song that only iKON can do. This video proves it. So, thanks to Hidden Track, which shared 'Dive' on YouTube, I'm glad the album is reaching out to more people.
